 SECURITY PRACTICES

- Follow OWASP security guidelines
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Never hardcode credentials or secrets
- Validate and sanitize all inputs
- Use HTTPS for all external communications
- Implement proper error handling that doesn't leak sensitive information
- Regular dependency updates and security scanning

## Data Protection
- Encrypt sensitive data at rest and in transit
- Implement proper access controls
- Use secure storage for credentials and secrets
- Implement data masking for sensitive information
- Follow data retention policies

## Secure Coding
- Prevent common vulnerabilities (SQL injection, XSS, CSRF)
- Use parameterized queries for database access
- Implement proper input validation and sanitization
- Use secure defaults for all configurations
- Implement proper session management

## Security Monitoring
- Log security-related events
- Implement monitoring for suspicious activities
- Regular security audits and penetration testing
- Document security incident response procedures
- Keep dependencies updated to prevent known vulnerabilities 


# Security Standards

## Secret Management
- Never commit secrets to repository
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Encrypt sensitive data
- Include .env in .gitignore
- Implement secrets rotation policy
- Document access control

## Dependency Management
- Regular security audits
- Automated vulnerability scanning
- License compliance checks

